<FIRST>u i AM-Japan-Markets     03-03 0216</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Japan-Markets,0222</SECOND>
<HEAD>Dollar Almost Unchanged Against Yen, Stocks Off</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The U.S. dollar was almost unchanged Friday against
the Japanese yen in Tokyo, while stock prices declined slightly.
   The dollar opened at 128.58 yen, up 0.51 yen from Thursday's
closing, and ranged between 128.10 and 128.70 yen during the day. It
finished the week at 128.12 yen, up a slight 0.05 yen.
   On the Tokyo Stock Exchange, the Nikkei Stock Average of 225
selected issues, which gained 22.67 points Thursday, lost 73.63
points, or 0.22 percent, closng at 32,000.10.
   Dealers said the dollar was holding its strength against the yen
following a West German decision to keep interest rates unchanged.
   Bundesbank, the West German central bank, announced Thursday it
would maintain its official discount rate at 4.0 percent and its
Lombard interest rate at 6.0 percent.
   ``The dollar may move up to 129 yen in the near future,'' said a
dealer at a major Tokyo bank, speaking on condition of anonymity.
``But it would take a real effort on the part of the market to push
it up to 130 yen.''
   On the stock exchange, the Nikkei index shot up 226.34 points
within minutes of the market's opening, but began declining toward
the end of the morning session because of profit-taking, traders
said.
</TEXT>
