<FILEID>AP-NR-03-03-89 1525EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>u f PM-WallStreet3pm     03-03 0287</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Wall Street 3pm,0303</SECOND>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The stock market showed some scattered gains
today in an indecisive session.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials rose 8.04 to 2,273.75 by
3 p.m. on Wall Street.
   Gainers outnumbered losers by about 4 to 3 in nationwide trading
of New York Stock Exchange-listed issues, with 780 up, 587 down and
524 unchanged.
   The Commerce Department reported that the index of leading
economic indicators rose 0.6 percent in January, in line with
advance estimates on the Street.
   The figures elicited no strong response from the bond market,
where prices were mixed.
   In the absence of any stimulus from that direction, brokers said,
money managers at investing institutions continued some selective
buying of stocks in the hopes of showing good results when they make
their first-quarter reports to clients at the end of this month.
   But otherwise, traders seemed reluctant to make any big
commitments.
   TW Services fell ~ to 27. A Delaware court upheld the ``poison
pill'' defense the company is employing to fight a takeover bid by
Coniston Partners.
   Among actively traded blue chips, Texaco rose { to 53; Union
Carbide gained 1\ to 31~; American Express rose \ to 30\, and Exxon
was unchanged at 44[.
   Federal Home Loan Mortgage preferred shares picked up ~ to 53. A
Senate bill has been introduced that calls for the conversion of the
shares to common stock and the installation of a board of directors.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks rose
.50 to 163.71. At the American Stock Exchange, the market value
index was up 1.06 at 326.01.
   Volume on the Big Board came to 121.96 million shares with an
hour to go.
</TEXT>
