<FIRST>r f AM-EmployerOutlook     03-03 0073</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Employer Outlook,0076</SECOND>
<HEAD>30 Percent Of Employers Foresee Staff Expansion</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Thirty percent of U.S. employers plan to increase
their staff in the April-June period, while 6 percent foresee
cutbacks, according to a survey of 14,000 companies by Manpower
Inc., the temporary help agency.
   ``Labor shortages continue unabated, especially in major
cities,'' Manpower said. A year earlier, 29 percent had predicted
staff increases and 6 percent had forecast cuts.
</TEXT>
