<FIRST>r f AM-MortgageRates     03-03 0073</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Mortgage Rates,0077</SECOND>
<HEAD>Fixed-Rate Mortgages Averaging 10.91 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fixed-rate home mortgages are currently
averaging 10.91 percent, according to a national survey released
Friday by the Federal Home Loan Mortgage Corp.
   That rate was up from a rate of 10.78 percent last week.
   On one-year adjustable rate mortgages, lenders were asking an
average initial rate of 8.91 percent this week, up from 8.73 percent
the week before, Freddie Mac said.
</TEXT>
