   The stock market pieced together a moderate gain
Friday in a quiet session.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials rose 8.58 to 2,274.29,
stretching its gain for the week to 28.75 points.
   Advancing issues outnumbered declines by about 3 to 2 in
nationwide trading of New York Stock Exchange-listed stocks, with
865 up, 582 down and 498 unchanged.
   Volume on the floor of the Big Board came to 151.79 million
